;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;

; See character-encoding-test.lisp for a description of this file.

;;;;;;;;;;
; **NOTE added by Matt Kaufmann 3/22/2026 during preparation of Version 8.7 release**

; When using ACL2 built on Allegro CL 10.1, certification failed after the
; addition of this file as character-encoding-test.acl2 when using cert.pl
; (hence, during a regression).  But certificcation succeeded when starting
; such an ACL2 and then evaluationg:
;   (ld "character-encoding-test.acl2")
;   (certify-book "character-encoding-test" ?)

; I checked that the 2-byte UTF-8 character at issue occurred as expected in
; character-encoding-test.cert.out after the failed attempt.

; The only explanation that occurs to me is that a character can get changed as
; cert.pl processes files.  I'm baffled, this is an odd case, and I don't want
; to hold up the release.  I could just remove this book from the regression
; suite for Allegro CL, but I suspect that this issue could come up in the
; future for other Lisps or platforms.  It would be good to address this issue,
; but there are many improvements ready for a release and I don't want to delay
; it.  So to get on with the release, I'm simply moving this file.

; End of **NOTE**.
;;;;;;;;;;

; Like character-encoding-test.lisp, this file has been saved using the utf-8
; character-encoding. Take care that your editor does not convert this file to
; another encoding.

(defun test-1 () "ó")

(defthm len-test-1
  (equal (length (test-1)) 2)
  :rule-classes nil)
